===== Data Ingestion with Document Loader =====
i) Text Loader -> its help you load any type of text file.
When we are loading this entire content in the speech.txt will be converted into a document only when we write loader.load().

from langchain_community.document_loaders import TextLoader

loader = TextLoader('speech.txt')
#loader -> object of document type
text_document = loader.load()
text_document # You will able to see the content along with metadata information

ii) PyPDF -> Reading a PDF file 

from langchain_community.document_loaders import PyPDFLoader
loader1 = pyPDFLoader('attention.pdf')
docs= loader1.load()
docs
type(docs) #List
type(docs[0]) # Document Type

iii) Web Based Loader  

Using web_paths, we can read any number of urls using "," comma seperator.
When web_path, use 1 url. If we use web_paths, then we can use multiple url's.

Here you need bs4(beautiful Soup), when you need to perfrom the scraping task in your project.

from langchain_community.document_loaders import WebBasedLoader
import bs4

loader2 = WebBasedLoader(web_paths=("https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/integrations/document_loaders",),
bs_kwargs=dict(parse_only=bs4.SoupStrainer(class_=("post-title","post-content","post-header"))))
loader2.load()

iv) Arxiv => arXiv is an open-access archive for 2 million scholarly articles in the fields of physics, mathematics, computer science, quantitative biology, quantitative finance, statistics, electrical engineering and systems science, and economics.

from langchain_community.document_loaders import ArxivLoader

# Supports all arguments of `ArxivAPIWrapper`
docs = ArxivLoader(
    query="1706.03762", # Attention is all you need research paper
    load_max_docs=2, # maximum it will load 2 documents
    # doc_content_chars_max=1000,
    # load_all_available_meta=False,
    # ...
)

lens(docs)

v) Wikipedia 

from langchain_community.document_loaders import WikipediaLoader
docs = WikipediaLoader(query="Generative AI", load_max_docs=2).load()
len(docs)
print(docs)


======= Recursive Character Text Splitter ======
This text splitter that is recursive character text splitter is the recommended one for the generic text. It is parameterized by a list of characters.
It tries to split on them in order until the chunks are small enough. The default list is ["\n\n","\n", " ",""]
They use these characters to probably do the splitting. 
this has the effect of trying to keep all the paragraphs and then sentences and then words together as long as possible.

. How the text is split: by the list of characters
. How the chunk size is measured : by number of characters


from langchain_community.document_loaders import pyPDFLoader
loader1 = pyPDFLoader('attention.pdf')
docs= loader1.load()
docs

We are going to take the entire pdf & then going to convert into text.

Q) How to recursively split the text by characters?
We need langchain_text_splitters moduke for that .

from langchain_text_splitters import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter

text_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(chunk_size=500,chunk_overlap=50)
final_documents =text_splitter.split_documents(docs)
final_documents
print(final_documents[0])
print(final_documents[1]) # Here you will see last 50 characters from final_documents[0] due to overlap size.

* create_documents will be useful when we use text-file 	


