Key Embedding Models
text-embedding-3-large: The most capable model, offering 3,072 dimensions, high performance for complex tasks, and strong multilingual support.
text-embedding-3-small: A highly efficient, smaller model that outperforms text-embedding-ada-002 while being faster and cheaper.
text-embedding-ada-002: A previous-generation standard model, widely used for general purposes with 1,536 dimensions

from langchain_openai import OpenAIEmbeddings
embeddings= OpenAIEmbeddings(model="text-embedding-3-large")
embeddings

Text = "This is tutorial on OPENAI Embedding"

*** Note - Remember this OpenAI embedding is not completely for free because there will be some charges that will be applied for this particular embedding.
query_result=embedding.embed_query(text) #converted text into vectors
query_result 
len(query_result[0]) # 3072 -> So what it does is that it takes this entire sentence and it converts into a vector of 3072 dimension.

If we want we can set our own dimension as well.
embeddings_1024= OpenAIEmbeddings(model="text-embedding-3-large",dimensions=1024)
query_result_1024=embeddings_1024.embed_query(text)
len(query_result_1024[0]) #1024

