=============== Vector Stores ===============
FAISS 
CDHROMA DB
ASTRA DB -> it Uses Cassandra DB

FAISS -> FAISS(Facebook AI Similarity Search. it is a library for efficient similarity search and clustering of dense vectors. 
It contains algorithms that search in a set of vectors of any size, up to ones that possibly do not fit in the RAM.
It also contains supporting code for evaluation and parameter tuning.

from langchain_community.document_loaders import TextLoader
from langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS
from langchain_community.embeddings import OllamaEmbeddings
from langchain_text_splitters import CharacterTextSplitter

loader=TextLoader('speech.txt')
documents=loader.load()
text_splitter=CharacterTextSplitter(chunk_size=1000,chunk_overlap=30)
docs=text_splitter.split_documents(documents)

embeddings=OllamaEmbeddings()
db=FAISS.from_documents(docs,embeddings)
db # <langchain_community.vectorstores.faiss.FAISS at >

# since it is running in my local machine.So it is going to take some amount of time for your system.

#querying 
query="What does the speaker believe is the main reason the United States enter the war?"
query="How does the speaker describe the desired ourcome of the war?"

docs=db.similarity_search(query)
docs 

->Whatever things are basically matching, we get every of these things right.

docs[0].page_content 

*** Retrieval -> we can also convert the vector stored into a retriever class.This allows us to easily use it in another langchain methods, which largely works with retriever.
this retrievers are like an interface, whenever we put any kind of query, it is just like connected to the vector store DB, only when we convert this vector store db in to retrieve a class.
so it lacks acts like an interface which will be able to retrieve the details from the vector store and provide you the response.

#Convert Vector DB into a Retriever
retriever=db.as_retriever()
retriever.invoke(query)

the reason of using this is that later on when we work with different, different LLM models,at that point of time, I cannot directly use vector store DB, 
but initially I need to convert this Vector DB into a retriever And then finally use it with any LLm Model.

*** Similarity Search with Score 
There are some FAISS specific methods.One of them is similarity_search_with_score, which allows you to return not only documents,
but also the distance score of the query to them.The return distance score is L2 distance, which is also called as Manhattan distance.
Therefore lower score is better.

docs_and_score =db.similarity_search_with_score(query)
docs_and_score #[Document(page_content='It is a distressing and oppressive duty,gentleman of the Congress',15552.862),

w.r.t. every information I get, there will be a score that will be attached. which is L2 score(Manhattan distance)

Q) can we not directly pass vectors instead of sentences?
-> Yes, we can do that. 

embedding_vector=embeddings.embed_query(query)
embedding_vector

docs_score = db.similarity_search_by_vector(embedding_vector)
docs_score

