### Saving & Loading 
db.save_local("faiss_index") => faiss_index is index name

Once I execute this, your file will be saved in the form of pickle & create a folder. Here you also have something called index.file (index.faiss,index.pkl)

new_db=FAISS.load("faiss_index",embeddings,allow_dangerous_deserialization=True)
# allow_dangerous_deserialization= True means , I trust this file & help me to deserialize it.
docs=new_db.similarity_search(query)
docs

========== 59 - Vector Stores & Retriever - Chroma DB =====================
Chroma DB : It is an AI native open source vector DB focused on developer productivity and happiness.Chroma is licensed under Apache 2.0.

Make sure you have installed Chroma DB

Step 1 : Building a sample vectordb
from langchain_chroma import Chroma
from langchain_community.document_loaders import TextLoader
from langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS
from langchain_community.embeddings import OllamaEmbeddings
from langchain_text_splitters import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter


loader=TextLoader('speech.txt')
data=loader.load()

#Split the data
text_splitter= RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(chunk_size=500,chunk_overlap=0)
splits = text_splitter.split_documents(data)

embeddings= OllamaEmbeddings()
vectordb=Chroma.from_documents(splits,embedding=embedding)
vectordb

#query the db
query = " When does the speaker believe is the main reason the United States should enter the war?"
docs=vectordb.similarity_search(query)
docs[0].page_content

# save it in the local/disk
vectordb2=Chroma.from_documents(splits,embedding=embedding,persist_directory="./chroma_db")
Above  command creates a sqllite3 db. Every vector will be stored in this DB.

#load from the local/disk
db2 = Chroma(persist_directory="./chroma_db",embedding_function=embedding)
dcos=db2.similarity_search(query)
print(docs[0].page_content)

#Similarity search with score
docs = vectordb2.similarity_search_with_score(query)
docs 

###Retriever option
retriever=vectordb2.as_retriever()
retriever.invoke(query)[0].page_content
